<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="un1013q"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un1" href="#un1013">UN1: </a>  <a href="../../ff/unbs/un1all.htm#un1013q"> (NLI.3) 13(q)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Manas (specific cognition)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Instead of recognising itself to be Brahman, it <font color="green">[the unenlightened soul]</font> blindly identifies itself with its adjuncts (Up&amacr;dhis), and thus looks for its true Self in the body, the sense-organs, and in the internal organ <mark>(Manas)</mark>, i.e., the organ of specific cognition. <small> <a name="THRdec1908" href="/udra/udex.htm#thrdec1908"><cite title="source">The Theosophical Review</cite></a> (December 1908), Hedwig S. Albarus, &ldquo;Modern Idealism and the Ved&amacr;ntic Philosophy&rdquo; 351</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c07256d" href="../../../f/ff/fnbs/c07all.htm#c07256d">VI.C.07:256(d)</a> </dd> </dd></dl>
